# Global menu wiring (Unity / XFCE model)

Ooze is a Mutter Wayland compositor. Match the desktop contracts those DEs use:

## Wayland GTK (Spot, Command, modern GTK3/4)

1. Compositor advertises `gtk_shell1` **GLOBAL_APP_MENU** by keeping
   `meta_prefs_set_show_fallback_app_menu(FALSE)` (see `my_plugin_apply_wm_preferences`).
2. Clients export over the session bus; Mutter exposes paths on `MetaWindow`:
   - `gtk-unique-bus-name`
   - `gtk-menubar-object-path` (prefer) or `gtk-app-menu-object-path` (fallback)
   - `gtk-application-object-path` / `gtk-window-object-path` for `app.*` / `win.*`
3. Shell binds `GDBusMenuModel` + `GDBusActionGroup`, restores focus, then activates
   (short defer so the client accepts focus — same idea as Unity panel clicks).

Apps must `gtk_application_set_menubar()` once at startup and
`gtk_application_window_set_show_menubar(..., FALSE)`.

## X11 / XFCE-style GTK modules

Install with `./scripts/install-appmenu.sh` (appmenu-gtk3-module + appmenu-registrar
+ xsettingsd).

Ooze sets `GTK_MODULES=appmenu-gtk-module` and `UBUNTU_MENUPROXY=1` in `run-devkit.sh`
and forwards them to dock-launched clients. Nested sessions keep **Xwayland** enabled
(omit `--no-x11`) because the module registers via X11 window IDs.

Registrar menus are **`com.canonical.dbusmenu`**, not `org.gtk.Menus`. Bind them with
`ooze-dbusmenu` (`GetLayout` / `Event`), never `GDBusMenuModel` (that yields unlabeled
"Menu" stubs). Prefer the registrar path when `GetMenuForWindow` succeeds.

Modern **appmenu-gtk-module** (Ubuntu 25.04+) often skips the registrar and exports
**`org.gtk.Menus`** via `_GTK_UNIQUE_BUS_NAME` / `_GTK_MENUBAR_OBJECT_PATH` instead.
For X11, if the registrar has nothing, bind those Mutter gtk-shell props with
`GDBusMenuModel` (same path as Wayland GTK apps). Do not treat that as the old
empty-stub fallthrough.

**Inkscape / classic GtkMenuBar:** must run on **Xwayland** (`GDK_BACKEND=x11`).
Spot, Command, dock, and King inject that for foreign apps; Ooze GTK4 apps force
Wayland. Native Wayland Inkscape **cannot** feed the global menu (`appmenu-gtk-module`
is not Wayland-native) — the panel shows “Needs X11 (Spot/Command)” instead of stubs.

X11 clients prefer registrar dbusmenu; if absent, bind modern appmenu’s
`org.gtk.Menus` export via gtk-shell props (not unlabeled stubs).

`Gtk/ShellShowsMenubar` hides the in-window bar. Prefer system `xsettingsd` when
installed; otherwise the compositor serves XSETTINGS itself (`compositor/ooze-xsettings.c`).
Optional host install: `./scripts/install-appmenu.sh`.

Do not invent a second menubar path per window for Ooze GtkApplication apps —
set the application menubar once.
Do not set Inkscape `window/menu` prefs to off — that removes the bar so nothing exports.

## Popup UX

Menu popups sit above windows with a dim scrim backdrop and a clear shadow so they
remain readable over light app chrome.
